The paper deals with compressive sensing and detection of signals, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), multimedia (cs.MM), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The use of measurement matrices and detectors also suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
